title.narrative: DSIF - Mozambique - Reinforcement and Extension of the National Power Transmission Grid

description.narrative: The project will provide access to energy through reinforcement and extension of the national power transmission grid. The government’s strategy for poverty reduction includes a focus on creating new jobs, increasing productivity and developing the private sector. These strategic aims all require a functional and nationwide energy infrastructure. The project includes construction of new power lines, extending the reach of the grid and improving substations.

sector.narrative: Electric power transmission and distribution (centralised grids)
